<h2 class="bac">Our Business:</h2>
<br>
<H3 class="bacg">Consumer Small Business Banking Technology and Operations</H3>
<p class="bacg">
&nbsp;provides end-to-end technology strategy and support to Consumer Small Business Banking as well as enterprise functions such as payments processing, cash servicing, fulfillment and reconcilement services and image strategy. 
</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>6,131 banking centers and more than 18,531 ATMs supported nationwide</li>
	<li>Manage 10,000 active check routes that contain over 46,000 scheduled stops</li>
	<li>Provides enterprise cash planning for vaults, banking centers, and ATMs with an average daily cash balance of $7.4 billion</li>
</ul>
<br>
<H3 class="bacg">Customer Service and Solutions</H3> 
<p class="bacg">
&nbsp;provides call, email, text chat and fulfillment support for Consumer, Card, Small Business, Business Card, Large Corporate and e-Commerce customers.  They also provide sales support for Deposit, Card and Small Business products; including fulfillment of all products sold in contact center and through online channels. 
</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>30 contact centers supported through our Contact Center Operations Team</li>
	<li>Total combined population of over 15,500 associates in Customer Service and Solutions</li>
</ul>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Overview:</h2>  
<p class="bac">
The Operations Management Analyst Program (OMAP) is an undergraduate program designed to provide external candidates and selected internal associates with an opportunity to prepare for future leadership positions in the bank&#39;s operational lines of business.  This high-visibility program will give participants the chance to experience assignments in both Consumer Small Business Banking Technology and Operations and Customer Service and Support.
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Qualifications:</h2>
<p class="bac">
Successful candidates will possess and demonstrate ability to work in a fast paced, empowered environment.  Ideal candidates will have the demonstrated ability to handle multiple, competing priorities and possess strong interpersonal skills.  Professional/academic experience will include strong technical/functional expertise.
</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Graduated from an accredited school with a bachelor&#39;s degree </li>
	<li>100% geographic flexibility within the United States during program participation period and upon graduation</li>
	<li>Willingness to work varied schedules, including swing shift for specific operations positions</li>
	<li>Solid organization skills, excellent planning ability, and project management skills</li>
	<li>Exceptional analytical and strong strategic thinking skills </li>
	<li>Ability to communicate effectively in both written and verbal communications </li>
</ul>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Training:</h2>
<p class="bac">
The program consists of the following developmental activities and opportunities:
</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>On-boarding; including Orientation and ongoing structured events</li>
	<li>Structured learning curriculum (including Six Sigma) and business critical assignments</li>
	<li>Monthly Program Meetings</li>
	<li>Mentoring and peer coach assignments</li>
	<li>Exposure to senior leadership teams and networking events</li>
</ul>

